    AsyncEventBus
    The Injection annotation used to look up Asynchronous Event Bus from the Molecule System.
    Doc

    DomainOperations
    An Inject annotation used to look up the domain operation instances being registed in the Molecule based system
    EventSink

    Fun

    Funs

Package com.github.bogieclj.molecule.system.annotations Description

This package holds the key annotations used to look up the respective services in Molecule Framework

AsyncEventBus - This annotation is used to look up the EventBus which can post messages asynchronously

Doc - This annotation is used to document an Fn

DomainOperations - This annotation is used to publish an Operation instance to the system

EventSink - This annotation is used to publish or register an EventSink.

Fun - This annotation is used to register an Fn in the system

Func - This annotation is used to register an Function in the system

Funs - This annotation is used to register a bunch of Fn in the system

Id - This annotation is used to attach a valid URI to a Function instance

In - This annotation is used to specify the In parameters expected by a Function in the system

LifecycleManagers - This annotation is used to register a LifecycleManager in the system

MainArgs - This annotation is used to inject the Arguments received by the java program on startup

Out - This annotation is used to specify the Out parameters provided by a Function in the system

ParamDecl - This annotation is used to declare the param information (whether In or Out) for a Function in the system

Shells - This annotation is used by Shell implementers to register an instance of Shell in the system

SyncEventBus - This annotation is used to look up the EventBus which can post messages synchronously
